page_id: S4-X-03
title: Sync conflict entry
description: Linux entry surface for C4-15 sync-conflict-detect and S4-X-09 C4-16/C4-21 replace confirmation.
banner:
  title: Sync conflict needs review
  message: AreaMatrix found files that may represent different versions. No version has been deleted.
  primary_action: Review
  secondary_action: Later
needs_review:
  title: Needs Review
  empty: No items need review.
  loading: Checking conflicts...
  error: Could not load review items
  retry: Try again
  disabled_review: Repair index first
  row_fields:
    - file name
    - relative path
    - conflict type
    - source platform
    - detected time
detail:
  banner: This file has a sync conflict
replace_confirm:
  page_id: S4-X-09
  title: Confirm Replace
  loading: Checking recovery options...
  confirmation: I understand this will replace the existing file.
  disabled_trash: Trash is unavailable and Core safety backup is unavailable. Use Keep both.
  missing_plan: Could not build replace plan.
  plan_source: SyncConflictEntryViewModel.ReplacePlanText
  plan_fields:
    - Old file path
    - New file path
    - Old hash
    - New hash
    - Affected record
    - Conflict or import item
    - Old version will be kept at
    - Database update
    - Change log
    - Recovery note
  apply: Replace
  success: change log action from resolve_sync_conflict
actions:
  load_conflicts: SyncConflictEntryViewModel.RefreshAsync
  review: SyncConflictEntryViewModel.ReviewRouteFor
  open_replace_confirm: SyncConflictEntryViewModel.OpenReviewRouteAsync
  preview_replace: SyncConflictEntryCoreBridge.PreviewSyncConflictResolutionAsync
  confirm_replace: SyncConflictEntryViewModel.ConfirmReplacePlan
  apply_replace: SyncConflictEntryViewModel.ApplyReplaceAsync
  later: SyncConflictEntryViewModel.DismissBanner
  detail_match: SyncConflictEntryViewModel.DetailConflictFor
safety:
  - The page calls detect_sync_conflicts through SyncConflictEntryCoreBridge.
  - The Linux entry filters status=NeedsReview before opening S4-X-09.
  - Later only hides the current banner and keeps the Needs Review list.
  - Review creates an S4-X-09 route and calls preview_sync_conflict_resolution with UseIncoming.
  - Replace stays disabled without Core preview token, Replace plan, reliable Trash/Core backup, and second confirmation.
  - Apply calls resolve_sync_conflict with replace_confirmed=true and an S4-X-09-C4-21 confirmation id.
  - The Linux UI does not directly delete, move, overwrite, or rename user files.
  - Missing conflict id disables Review and shows Repair index first.
